turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Come to think of it the real cause of that roue was Peter Burden.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Oh You knew there was nothing in that.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: I knew nothing of the sort.  You accepted presents from him.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Only a trivial little broach.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: I remember it well, covered in diamonds and the worst possible taste.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Not at all.  I quite like it.  I wear it often.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: You went out of your way to torture me over Peter Burden.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: [garbage], No, I didn't.  You worked the whole thing up in your jealous imagination.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: You must admit that he was in love with you. wasn't he?

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Oh, maybe a little.  Nothing serious.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: He let him kiss you.  You said you did.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Well, what of it.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: what of it?

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Well it gave him a lot of pleasure and it didn't hurt me.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: What about me?

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Well, if you hadn't been so nosey and suspicious you never would have known about it.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Well, that's a nice point of view I must say.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: I'm getting very bored with this conversation.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Me, too, bored stiff.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Do you want some brandy?

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: No thanks.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: I think I'll have a little.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: I don't see why you want it; you've already had two glasses.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: No particular reason.  Besides, they were little ones.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Well, it seems silly to go on and on with such a thing.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: You can hardly say- You can hardly call three little liquor glasses of brandy for the entire evening going on and on.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: It's becoming a habit with you.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: You needn't be so grand simply because you don't happen to want me at the moment.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Don't be stupid.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Amanda, really.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: What?

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Nothing.  Are you going out somewhere, darling?

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Just making myself fascinating for you.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Um- Well, that reply has just broken my heart.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: It's a woman's job to allure the man.  Watch me a moment, won't you?

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Oh, as a matter of fact, that's perfectly true.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: No, it isn't.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Yes, it is.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: No, it it is not, be quiet.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: It's a pity you didn't have a little bit more brandy.  It might have made you a little less disagreeable.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: hum, It doesn't seem to have worked such wonders with you.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: oh, Snap, snap, snap.  Like a little Adder.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Adders don't snap, they sting.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Nonsense, they've got a little bag of venom behind their fangs and they snap!

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: They sting.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: They snap.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Okay, I don't care if they roll about like hoops and bark, okay?

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: So, did you see much of Peter Burden after the divorce?

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Yes, I did quite a lot.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: You must have let him kiss you quite a good deal more then, huh?

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: [LAUGHTER] Mind your own business.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: I'm sure you had a riotous time, no restrain at all, very enjoyable.  You never had much anyway.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: You're quite insufferable.  I do imagine it's because you're drunk.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: I am not the slightest bit drunk.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: You always had a weak head.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: I do believe that I have said already that I had three minuet liquor glasses of brandy in the entire evening.  A child of two couldn't get drunk of that.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Oh, no on the contrary, a child of two could get violently drunk on only one glass.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Oh, really?  How about a child of three, or child of six, what about a child of nine?

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Not- Would you shut up.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: You know, we could get a really good debate going on about this.  You know intemperate tots.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: You're not very funny, dear.  You better have some more brandy.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: You know what?  That's a very good idea.  I think I will.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: You better turn that off, I think.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Why?

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Because it's very late and you'll disturb the people upstairs.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: There aren't any people upstairs.  It's a photography studio.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Well, there are people downstairs, I suppose.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: They're away in Tunis.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: This is no time of the year for Tunis.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Turn it on again, please.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: I do I shall do no such thing.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Very well.  If you have to be boorish and idiotic.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Turn it off.  It's driving me mad.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: You are far too temperamental.  Try to control yourself.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Turn it off!

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Go away!  Go away!  I- I hate you.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Very amusing indeed.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: You know what, I'm sick and tire of listening to you.  You're a-- You're a total sadistic bully.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Ja! Very funny.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Stop.  Would you just go away?  I mean, you're conceited, and overbearing, and utterly impossible.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: You are a vile tempered, wicked living, evil little beast.  And I hope I never set eyes on you ever again.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: This is the end! Do you understand me? This is the end.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Oh, you're not going like this.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Yes, I am. Let go with me

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: [GARBAGE] No, you're not.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: You are a cruel fiend and I-I loath you.  I thank God I realized who you are before I decided to marry you again.  Oh my God, never!

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: oh! Marry you again? I wouldn't marry you again if you came crawling to me on bended knee.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Beast

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: You're a wicked little vampire.  And I pray to God I never set eyes on you again as long as I live.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Brute

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: pig
